======================================================================
2. RAMANUJAN CONGRUENCES AND (2,3,5)
======================================================================

Ramanujan's partition congruences:
  p(5n+4) = 0 (mod 5)   for all n >= 0
  p(7n+5) = 0 (mod 7)   for all n >= 0
  p(11n+6) = 0 (mod 11) for all n >= 0

The moduli: 5, 7, 11
  5 = KEY1+KEY2
  7 = H_forb_1 = Phi_3(KEY1)
  11 = 2*KEY1+KEY1+KEY2 = 2*KEY1+KEY2+KEY1+KEY2... = f(KEY1*KEY2) + KEY1+KEY2? No...
  Actually: 5, 7, 11 are the 3rd, 4th, 5th primes

The residues: 4, 5, 6
  These are delta(p) = (p^2-1)/24:
  (5^2-1)/24 = 24/24 = 1... no, delta = (p-1)/? 

Verification:
  p(5*0+4) = p(4) = 5 = 0 mod 5? True
  p(5*1+4) = p(9) = 30 = 0 mod 5? True
  p(5*2+4) = p(14) = 135 = 0 mod 5? True
  p(5*3+4) = p(19) = 490 = 0 mod 5? True
  p(5*4+4) = p(24) = 1575 = 0 mod 5? True
  p(5*5+4) = p(29) = 4565 = 0 mod 5? True
  p(5*6+4) = p(34) = 12310 = 0 mod 5? True
  p(5*7+4) = p(39) = 31185 = 0 mod 5? True
  p(5*8+4) = p(44) = 75175 = 0 mod 5? True
  p(5*9+4) = p(49) = 173525 = 0 mod 5? True

  p(7*0+5) = p(5) = 7 = 0 mod 7? True
  p(7*1+5) = p(12) = 77 = 0 mod 7? True
  p(7*2+5) = p(19) = 490 = 0 mod 7? True
  p(7*3+5) = p(26) = 2436 = 0 mod 7? True
  p(7*4+5) = p(33) = 10143 = 0 mod 7? True
  p(7*5+5) = p(40) = 37338 = 0 mod 7? True
  p(7*6+5) = p(47) = 124754 = 0 mod 7? True
  p(7*7+5) = p(54) = 386155 = 0 mod 7? True

  p(11*0+6) = p(6) = 11 = 0 mod 11? True
  p(11*1+6) = p(17) = 297 = 0 mod 11? True
  p(11*2+6) = p(28) = 3718 = 0 mod 11? True
  p(11*3+6) = p(39) = 31185 = 0 mod 11? True
  p(11*4+6) = p(50) = 204226 = 0 mod 11? True
  p(11*5+6) = p(61) = 1121505 = 0 mod 11? True

All verified! The (2,3,5) triple appears as the modular structure:
  - The Ramanujan congruences use moduli KEY1+KEY2, Phi_3(KEY1), 11
  - The generating function is 1/prod(1-q^n) = 1/Euler function
  - The Dedekind eta function: eta(tau) = q^{1/24} * prod(1-q^n)
  - The 1/24 relates to |BT| = 24

