3. PARTITION AT TOURNAMENT-MEANINGFUL VALUES
======================================================================

p(n) at tournament-meaningful n values:
  p(  2) =               2  (KEY1           )  = 2
  p(  3) =               3  (KEY2           )  = 3
  p(  5) =               7  (KEY1+KEY2      )  = 7
  p(  6) =              11  (h(G2)          )  = 11
  p(  7) =              15  (H_forb_1       )  = 3 * 5
  p(  8) =              22  (rank(E8)       )  = 2 * 11
  p( 10) =              42  (V(Petersen)    )  = 2 * 3 * 7
  p( 12) =              77  (h(E6)          )  = 7 * 11
  p( 14) =             135  (dim(G2)        )  = 3 * 3 * 3 * 5
  p( 18) =             385  (h(E7)          )  = 5 * 7 * 11
  p( 21) =             792  (H_forb_2       )  = 2 * 2 * 2 * 3 * 3 * 11
  p( 24) =            1575  (|BT|           )  = 3 * 3 * 5 * 5 * 7
  p( 30) =            5604  (h(E8)          )  = 2 * 2 * 3 * 467
  p( 48) =          147273  (|BO|           )  = 3 * 7 * 7013
  p( 56) =          526823  (dim(V_E7)      )  = 11 * 47 * 1019
  p( 78) =        12132164  (dim(E6)        )  = 2 * 2 * 11 * 275731
  p(120) =      1844349560  (|BI|           )  = 2 * 2 * 2 * 5 * 47 * 981037

======================================================================
4. PENTAGONAL NUMBERS AND THE TOURNAMENT POLYNOMIAL
======================================================================

The pentagonal number theorem connects to the tournament polynomial:
  Euler: prod(1-q^n) = sum (-1)^k q^{k(3k-1)/2}
  The generalized pentagonal numbers: omega(k) = k(3k-1)/2

Generalized pentagonal numbers (both signs of k):
  k=+1: omega =    1, omega' =    2
  k=+2: omega =    5, omega' =    7
  k=+3: omega =   12, omega' =   15
  k=+4: omega =   22, omega' =   26
  k=+5: omega =   35, omega' =   40
  k=+6: omega =   51, omega' =   57

Pentagonal numbers omega_k = k(3k-1)/2:
  k=1: 1 = 1
  k=2: 5 = KEY1+KEY2
  k=3: 12 = h(E6)
  k=4: 22 = 2*11
  k=5: 35 = 5*7 = (KEY1+KEY2)*H_forb_1
  k=6: 51 = 3*17
  k=7: 70 = C(8,4) = C(rank(E8),4)
  k=8: 92 = 4*23
  k=9: 117

The coefficient 3 in k(3k-1)/2 is KEY2!
Pentagonal numbers = k(KEY2*k - 1)/2

The first few: 1, 5, 12, 22, 35, 51, 70, 92, ...
  Differences: 4, 7, 10, 13, 16, 19, 22, ...
  = arithmetic progression with common difference 3 = KEY2!

======================================================================
5. HOOK LENGTH FORMULA AND TOURNAMENTS
======================================================================

The hook length formula: f^lambda = n! / prod(hook lengths)
counts the number of standard Young tableaux of shape lambda.

SYT counts for rectangle shapes (a x b):
  (1x1), n= 1: f^lambda = 1 *
  (1x2), n= 2: f^lambda = 1 *
  (1x3), n= 3: f^lambda = 1 *
  (1x4), n= 4: f^lambda = 1 *
  (1x5), n= 5: f^lambda = 1 *
  (2x2), n= 4: f^lambda = 2 *
  (2x3), n= 6: f^lambda = 5 *
  (2x4), n= 8: f^lambda = 14 *
  (2x5), n=10: f^lambda = 42 *
  (3x3), n= 9: f^lambda = 42 *
  (3x4), n=12: f^lambda = 462
  (3x5), n=15: f^lambda = 6006
  (4x4), n=16: f^lambda = 24024
  (4x5), n=20: f^lambda = 1662804

SYT counts for staircase shapes (n, n-1, ..., 1):
  staircase(1) = [1], |lambda|=1: f^lambda = 1
  staircase(2) = [2, 1], |lambda|=3: f^lambda = 2
  staircase(3) = [3, 2, 1], |lambda|=6: f^lambda = 16
  staircase(4) = [4, 3, 2, 1], |lambda|=10: f^lambda = 768
  staircase(5) = [5, 4, 3, 2, 1], |lambda|=15: f^lambda = 292864
  staircase(6) = [6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1], |lambda|=21: f^lambda = 1100742656
  staircase(7) = [7, 6, 5, 4, 3, 2, 1], |lambda|=28: f^lambda = 48608795688960

======================================================================
6. CATALAN NUMBERS AND THEIR (2,3) CONTENT
======================================================================

Catalan numbers C_n = C(2n,n)/(n+1):
  C_ 0 =        1
  C_ 1 =        1
  C_ 2 =        2 = KEY1
  C_ 3 =        5 = KEY1+KEY2
  C_ 4 =       14 = dim(G2)
  C_ 5 =       42 = f(9) = 2*H_forb_2
  C_ 6 =      132 = dim(so(12))
  C_ 7 =      429 = 3*11*13
  C_ 8 =     1430 = 2*5*11*13
  C_ 9 =     4862 = 2*11*13*17
  C_10 =    16796
  C_11 =    58786
  C_12 =   208012
  C_13 =   742900
  C_14 =  2674440

Catalan numbers at tournament-meaningful indices:
  C_2 = 2 = KEY1
  C_3 = 5 = KEY1+KEY2
  C_4 = 14 = dim(G2)
  C_5 = 42 = f(9) = 2*H_forb_2
  C_6 = 132 = dim(so(12))... 

  C_3/C_2 = 5/2 = (KEY1+KEY2)/KEY1 = |BI|/|BO|
  C_4/C_3 = 14/5
  C_5/C_4 = 42/14 = 3 = KEY2
  C_6/C_5 = 132/42 = 22/7 ~ pi!

======================================================================
7. THE PARTITION FUNCTION MOD 2 AND MOD 3
======================================================================

p(n) mod 2 — distribution:
  p(n) even: 42/100, p(n) odd: 58/100

p(n) mod 2 for n=0..49:
  n= 0-9: 1101111100
  n=10-19: 0011101110
  n=20-29: 1001100001
  n=30-39: 0011011111
  n=40-49: 0101100011

p(n) mod 3 for n=0..49:
  n= 0-9: [1, 1, 2, 0, 2, 1, 2, 0, 1, 0]
  n=10-19: [0, 2, 2, 2, 0, 2, 0, 0, 1, 1]
  n=20-29: [0, 0, 0, 1, 0, 2, 0, 1, 1, 2]
  n=30-39: [0, 2, 0, 0, 1, 0, 1, 1, 2, 0]
  n=40-49: [0, 0, 2, 0, 1, 1, 0, 2, 0, 2]

