8. SUMMARY
======================================================================

======================================================================
PARTITION — TOURNAMENT DICTIONARY
======================================================================

Connection                           Value              Meaning
----------------------------------------------------------------------
p(5) = 7                             5=KEY1+KEY2        H_forb_1 partitions
p(6) = 11                            6=h(G2)            H_forb_1 + 4
p(7) = 15                            7=H_forb_1         next forbidden
p(8) = 22                            8=rank(E8)         largest exceptional
p(10) = 42                           10=V(Petersen)     h(E8) partitions
p(12) = 77                           12=h(E6)           77 = 7*11
p(30) = 5604                        30=h(E8)           5604 = 2^2*3*467

Ramanujan congruences mod (KEY1+KEY2, H_forb_1, 11)
Pentagonal recurrence coefficient = KEY2
Catalan: C_2=KEY1, C_3=KEY1+KEY2, C_4=dim(G2), C_5=f(9)
Euler's pentagonal numbers grow at rate KEY2*k^2/2

p(7) = 15 = C(6,2) = C(h(G2),2)
The number of partitions of H_forb_1 equals the number of edges of K_{h(G2)}!
